Real World Challenge - API Mashathon, with HP IDOL OnDemand


# Deployment Instructions

## Organization of Submission

The given application basically does sentiment analysis on video/audio files hosted publicly using various **Idol OnDemand APIs**. And sends the analysis result via mail using **Cloud-Elements**.

The chat feature is an integral part of the application which behaves as a normal chat application using **Pusher API** and has a **mood-meter** to analyze the mood of the participants based on the chat texts using again, **Idol OnDemand API**.

As per the requirement to mash up APIs – HP Idol OnDemand and one/few of the listed 3rd party APIs, to create a solution targeting a real world business scenario.

This is a standard AngularJS, NodeJS and ExpressJS application with Bootstrap for styling UI           elements.

Basically, the node server kicks the index.js. It then loads my index.html file, the index.html plugs my Angular application to the UI. Then Angular handles all the routing mechanism. Please go through the code-walkthrough to get detailed description about the application architecture.

#Application Setup

Please go through the provided deployment video along with the submission, in case of any difficulties.

To successfully launch the application, you need to have NodeJS installed in your machine.

Once NodeJS is successfully installed. To test the installation, type **node –v** and **npm –v**. If it returns some # version, we are in good shape to run our application.

Unzip the source code provided. Navigate to the extracted directory and launch the terminal from the same directory. Type **npm install** for installing the node modules. Type **node index.js** in the terminal, which will start the server.


The directory structure would be something like as follows:-

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

Now open the web browser and navigate to localhost:5000. You would be getting the page which follows below.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

If you've made it this far. You've made it, have fun.
